{% submission %}

{% submission-part type="problem" %}

I want to be able to give students different tests, so they can't just sit and wait for their table partner to answer the question on the screen and then copy off of them. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% submission-part type="proposed-solution" %}

I think a system where I could build banks of questions on various content, that then could be pulled from for the test so that everyone get randomized questions rather than the same questions in random order. I could set up the test asking it to pull 3 questions from my ecology multiple choice bank (which may have 20 questions), 1 from ecology short answer bank (which may have 5), etc.  So that when the students take the test no 2 tests are the same, or have the same questions. Even more helpful is if I could rank the difficulty of the questions so that no one accidentally gets only easy or only hard questions. Add in the ability to share and collaborate with other teachers,  make it a Google Form or any other helpful adaptation would be awesome. Including being able to print the tests and auto grading.

{% /submission-part %}

{% /submission %}